    "### Behavioural trend features\n",
    "\n",
    "* BILL_SLOPE_6M\n",
    "* PAY_SLOPE_6M\n",
    "\n",
    "This is textbook strong credit-risk feature engineering.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Key Observations From Summary Statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "## PAY_RATIO variables\n",
    "\n",
    "Median values:\n",
    "~0.04–0.10\n",
    "\n",
    "This means:\n",
    "\n",
    "Most customers pay only 4–10% of their outstanding balance monthly.\n",
    "Means are extremely large (100–230+), and max values are massive.\n",
    "\n",
    "That indicates:\n",
    "\n",
    "Extreme outliers when bill amounts are small and payments large.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is heavily skewed.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Important Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "PAY_RATIO features are:\n",
    "\n",
    "* Informative\n",
    "* But highly skewed\n",
    "* May require:\n",
    "\n",
    "  * Capping\n",
    "  * Log transformation\n",
    "  * Winsorizing\n",
    "\n",
    "Tree-based models handle this better than linear models.\n",
    "\n",
    "## UTILIZATION6M_MEAN\n",
    "\n",
    "Mean ≈ 0.37\n",
    "Median ≈ 0.28\n",
    "\n",
    "Interpretation:\n",
    "\n",
    "Average customer uses ~37% of credit limit.\n",
    "Some customers exceed 1.0 (max ≈ 5.36)\n",
    "\n",
    "Meaning:\n",
    "They exceed credit limit — very risky behaviour.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a strong risk indicator.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Delinquency Summary Features\n",
    "\n",
    "MONTHS_LATE_6M:\n",
    "\n",
    "Median = 0\n",
    "75% = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "So:\n",
    "Most customers had 0 or 1 late month.\n",
    "\n",
    "MAX_DELAY_6M:\n",
    "Median = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "This confirms:\n",
    "Delinquency is concentrated in a smaller risky group.\n",
    "These features compress the PAY_* variables into powerful summary signals.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trend Features (SLOPE)\n",
    "\n",
    "BILL_SLOPE_6M mean ≈ -2631\n",
    "PAY_SLOPE_6M mean ≈ -171\n",
    "\n",
    "Interpretation:\n",
