    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Dissertation-Ready Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "You can use this:\n",
    "\n",
    "> The engineered feature set expands the original dataset to 42 variables by incorporating behavioural ratios, utilization measures, delinquency aggregates, and temporal trend features. Payment-to-balance ratios exhibit strong right skewness, indicating substantial heterogeneity in repayment behaviour. Utilization metrics show that, on average, customers use approximately 37% of their available credit, with extreme outliers exceeding credit limits. Aggregated delinquency measures confirm that most customers exhibit no recent delays, while a smaller subset displays concentrated high-risk behaviour. Trend-based slope features capture dynamic changes in billing and repayment patterns, enabling detection of deteriorating financial behaviour. Together, these engineered variables enhance the model’s ability to capture non-linear behavioural risk signals beyond static demographic attributes.\n",
